<h2>How to Choose the Right Free AI Tool</h2>
<p><strong>Need a general AI assistant?</strong> ChatGPT's free tier is highly versatile — it handles writing, coding, research, and analysis in one tool. Claude is a strong alternative for longer documents. Gemini excels if you need real-time web search and multimodal capabilities.</p>
<p><strong>Need free AI image generation?</strong> Leonardo AI's 150 daily tokens are highly generous. Ideogram is essential if your images need readable text. Stable Diffusion is ideal if you want unlimited generations (requires a GPU).</p>
<p><strong>Need free AI coding help?</strong> Cursor gives you a full AI-powered editor for free. v0.dev is perfect for generating React components.</p>
<p><strong>Need free AI video editing?</strong> CapCut offers professional features completely free, though exports include a watermark. Runway is better for AI video generation from text prompts.</p>
<p><strong>Need free AI voice or music?</strong> ElevenLabs for realistic voiceovers, Suno for original music generation — both have generous free tiers.</p>
<p><strong>Need free AI design tools?</strong> Canva is a highly versatile free design platform with AI features built in. Adobe Firefly is great for photo editing and generative fill.</p>

<h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

<h3>What is the best free AI tool overall?</h3>
<p>ChatGPT offers a highly versatile free AI tool with powerful conversation, writing, coding, and analysis capabilities. For specific tasks, Cursor (coding), Canva (design), and CapCut (video editing) are top choices in their categories.</p>

<h3>Are free AI tools really free?</h3>
<p>Most offer genuine free tiers with real functionality. The trade-offs are daily usage caps, watermarks on exports, or slower speeds during peak times. For light to moderate use, free tiers are often surprisingly capable.</p>

<h3>What is the best free AI image generator?</h3>
<p>Leonardo AI offers a highly generous free tier with 150 daily tokens. Ideogram excels at generating images with accurate text. Stable Diffusion is completely free and open-source.</p>

<h3>What is the best free AI coding assistant?</h3>
<p>Cursor offers a leading free AI coding experience with a purpose-built AI editor. GitHub Copilot also provides a free tier, and v0.dev is excellent for frontend developers.</p>

<h3>What is the best free AI video editor?</h3>
<p>CapCut is a top choice with professional-grade AI features completely free. The main limitation is a watermark on exports.</p>

<h3>Is Google Gemini free to use?</h3>
<p>Yes, Google Gemini has a completely free tier with access to Gemini Pro 2.0. It offers real-time web search, image understanding, file uploads, and integration with Google services — all at no cost with generous daily usage limits.</p>

<h3>What is the best free AI search engine?</h3>
<p>Perplexity AI is a top free AI search engine, combining conversational AI with real-time web search. It provides cited answers with source links, making it ideal for research and fact-finding.</p>

<h3>Can I use free AI tools for commercial projects?</h3>
<p>It depends on the tool and its terms of service. Most free tiers allow personal and educational use, but commercial usage may require paid plans. ChatGPT allows commercial use of outputs. Canva's free tier allows commercial use of designs. Always check each platform's specific licensing terms.</p>

